nd stands on a granite base in the enclos' cemetery. The pedestal carries references to {{quotation|\" L\u2019AN 1909 MISSION. L\u2019AN 1891 MISSION. L\u2019AN 1593 POSEE. L\u2019AN 1891 RESTAUREE\"|}}The octagonal shaft carries a statue of either Saint Peter or Saint Cl\u00e9ment and above his head an escutcheon carries the depiction of a dove who holds a twig in his beak. This was the coat of arms of Abbot Briant, the Abbot of Land\u00e9vennec from 1608 to 1632.  The crosspiece also bears the arms of abbot Tanguy and an inscription reading \"IAN GVEN-QUALEC, Y. GAL 1617\".  On the crosspiece and on either side of the depiction of Jesus on the cross are statues of the Virgin Mary, her hands clasped and her eyes tearful (she is back to back with a statue depicting an apostle) and John the Evangelist whose head is turned slightly towards Jesus. He is paired back to back with a female saint. On the reverse of Jesus on the cross is a depiction of him seated on a globe, his hands raised. He wears a sash bearing the words \"GARDE QU\u2019IL FERA LE ROY ESTANT JUGERA\". To his right an angel blows on a trumpet and on his left a supplicant wrapped in a shroud stands awaiting judgement, his eyes closed. At the foot of the calvary is a small kersanton stone altar added in 1617.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.croix-finistere.com/commune/argol/argol.html|title=Website covering calvaries and crosses in Finistere|accessdate=8 June 2015|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130308031019/http://www.croix-finistere.com/commune/argol/argol.html|archive-date=8 March 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Statues of Saint Peter and Saint Paul==\nThere are 17th century statues of both these saints in the sanctuary.\n\n==The master altar==\n[[File:Photo0747.eglise Argol.jpg|thumb|centre|200px|Statue of Saint Peter]]\nThis includes a stained glass window dedicated to Saint Peter and a 1.20m statue of Saint Peter carved from wood and dating to the 16th century. He holds an open book in one hand and