 door to the presbytery are three statues. In the centre is a \"pi\u00e9ta\" believed to have been part of a calvary. The other sculptures are a statue of Saint Tugen in the dress of a bishop and holding a bunch of keys and a statue depicting John the Baptist.\n\n==See also==\n{{portal bar|Architecture|Catholicism|France|History}}\n{{Commons category|Enclos paroissial d'Argol}}\n*[[Culture of France]]\n*[[French architecture]]\n*[[History of France]]\n*[[Religion in France]]\n*[[Roman Catholicism in France]]\n<!-- please keep entries in alphabetical order -->\n\n==Recommended reading==\n\"Sculpteurs sur pierre en Basse-Bretagne. Les Ateliers du XVe au XVIIe Si\u00e8cle\" by Emmanuelle LeSeac'h. Published by Presses Universitaires de Rennes. {{ISBN|978-2-7535-3309-7}}.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{coord|48.2464|-4.3170|type:landmark_region:FR|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Churches in Finist\u00e8re]]\n[[Category:Calvaries in Brittany]]\n[[Category:Ossuaries]]\n[[Category:Parish closes in Brittany]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "replaced: 17th century \u2192 17th-century", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argol_Parish_close"}
